  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen trying to send a transaction on Optimistic Kovan and setting the `gasLimit` via `estimateGas`, the last 4 digits consistently contain a 5 in the significant digit, see screenshot below:\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to Metamask on Optimistic Kovan\r\n2. Click to send an ERC20 transfer\r\n3. See gasLimit value\r\n4. Send tx and get RPC error `Invalid transaction: exceeds block gas limit\"\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nthe leading 5 in the L2GasLimit should be a 0.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n<img width=\"345\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-06-24 at 4 48 24 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5341583/123345928-253a0e00-d525-11eb-94ff-7c8d877c6dae.png\">\r\n\r\n",
